graph TD
    A[Start: Client is responsible for caring for sick, elderly, or disabled family members]

    A --> B{Does the dependent require constant supervision or care?}

    B --> B1[Yes]
    B1 --> C{Is professional in-home care accessible and acceptable to the client and dependent?}
    C --> C1[Yes]
    C1 --> D{Is professional in-home care affordable or covered by insurance or subsidies?}
    D --> D1[Yes]
    D1 --> E[Arrange professional in-home care; assist with applications and logistics]
    D --> D2[No]
    D2 --> F{Is the client eligible for government assistance programs for caregiving?}
    F --> F1[Yes]
    F1 --> G[Help client apply for subsidies/programs to afford in-home care]
    F --> F2[No]
    F2 --> H{Are there non-profit organizations offering caregiving support or grants?}
    H --> H1[Yes]
    H1 --> I[Connect client with non-profit caregiving services; assist with applications]
    H --> H2[No]
    H2 --> J{Can family or friends assist with caregiving duties?}
    J --> J1[Yes]
    J1 --> K[Coordinate shared caregiving schedule with family/friends]
    J --> J2[No]
    J2 --> L{Is the client willing and able to become a paid caregiver through government programs?}
    L --> L1[Yes]
    L1 --> M[Assist client in applying to become a paid caregiver]
    L --> L2[No]
    L2 --> N{Is respite care available to provide temporary relief?}
    N --> N1[Yes]
    N1 --> O[Schedule respite care; explore part-time or flexible work options]
    N --> N2[No]
    N2 --> P[Explore long-term solutions and advocate for additional support; consider legal advice]

    B --> B2[No]
    B2 --> Q{Can the dependent stay alone safely for certain periods?}
    Q --> Q1[Yes]
    Q1 --> R{Is the client open to employment during those periods?}
    R --> R1[Yes]
    R1 --> S[Identify jobs with suitable hours matching care availability]
    R --> R2[No]
    R2 --> T{Is remote work from home feasible given caregiving duties?}
    T --> T1[Yes]
    T1 --> U[Explore remote employment opportunities; assist with necessary training]
    T --> T2[No]
    T2 --> V{Is the client experiencing barriers such as stress or burnout?}
    V --> V1[Yes]
    V1 --> W[Refer client to caregiver support groups and counseling resources]
    V --> V2[No]
    V2 --> X[Reassess situation for potential solutions]

    Q --> Q2[No]
    Q2 --> Y{Can technology assist in monitoring the dependent safely?}
    Y --> Y1[Yes]
    Y1 --> Z[Implement monitoring systems; client works nearby or from home]
    Y --> Y2[No]
    Y2 --> AA{Are adult day care or community programs available and acceptable?}
    AA --> AA1[Yes]
    AA1 --> AB[Assist in enrolling dependent in day programs; arrange transportation if needed]
    AA --> AA2[No]
    AA2 --> AC{Cultural or personal reluctance to accept outside help?}
    AC --> AC1[Yes]
    AC1 --> AD[Provide counseling on benefits of support; address concerns sensitively]
    AC --> AC2[No]
    AC2 --> AE{Language or communication barriers in accessing services?}
    AE --> AE1[Yes]
    AE1 --> AF[Provide translation services; connect with culturally appropriate resources]
    AE --> AE2[No]
    AE2 --> AG[Explore alternative community support options]

    E & G & I & K & M & O & S & U & W & Z & AB & AD & AF & AG & P & X --> END[End: Tailored Action Plan addressing caregiving responsibilities]
